I use an 3rdparty library. The library contains an interface with two inner interfaces:

public interface IModel
{
  ...
    public static interface Info
    {
        public abstract Aspects getAspects();
    }

    public static interface Callbacks
    {
        public abstract void reset(ServletRequest servletrequest);

        public abstract void validate(ServletRequest servletrequest, AspectErrors aspecterrors);
    }
}

The classes Aspects and AspectErrors are also from the 3rdparty library. Now i create an own class Test2. After creation the class will be adapted. The class should implement the interfaces IModel.Info and IModel.Callbacks:

public class Test2 implements IModel.Info, IModel.Callbacks {
}

I add the implements clause and import the IModel interface using shortcut Ctrl+Shift+M. After that i use Quick Fix to add unimplemented methods. Now java.lang.IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.

I think the problem is the syntax. If i change the implements clause in the following manner:

public class Test2 implements Info, Callbacks {
}

and change the imports so that no IModel but IModel.Info and IModel.Callbacks will be imported, the unimplemented methods will be generated using Quick Fix.
